        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> As some of you may or may not have heard, 'Project M' has been put on indefinite hold by SOE.  'Project M' was an effort to allow Players to take control of NPCs.  </P><P>For an all-to-brief time on Test, players were could chose to take control of a random newbie monster when they logged in, instead of playing a character.  The rat or fire beetle could attack PCs and level up...but all gains were lost when you were killed or logged out.</P><P>This was the only form of PvP in EQ I have ever actually enjoyed.  It was fun for both the monsters and the players.  Its passing should be mourned.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>

      </tr>

